Standard and Poor's said it isreviewing &lt;MEPC Plc's> two A-rated eurobond issues totalling125 mln stg for a possible downgrade.    The review follows the agreement by the British-basedreal-estate firm to acquire a controlling interest in OldhamEstate Plc and its offer to buy the remaining equity.    The maximum cost of the acquisition would be 620.9 mln stg.The purchase owuld be financed largely by equity, butuncertainties exist as to the amount of debt to be assumed byMEPC and the quality of the properties in Oldham's portfolio, Sand P said. Reuter&#3;